\textbf{FUTURE-AI: Guiding Principles and Consensus Recommendations for Trustworthy Artificial Intelligence in Future Medical Imaging}

\textbf{Abstract}

Artificial intelligence (AI) is poised to transform medical imaging, with the potential to improve the quality of care, reduce costs, and increase access to care. However, the widespread adoption of AI in medical imaging is contingent on the development of trustworthy AI systems. In this paper, we present the consensus recommendations of the Future of Artificial Intelligence in Medical Imaging (FUTURE-AI) working group, a multidisciplinary group of experts in medical imaging, AI, and ethics. The FUTURE-AI working group was convened by the American College of Radiology (ACR) and the Radiological Society of North America (RSNA) to develop a set of guiding principles and consensus recommendations for trustworthy AI in medical imaging. The FUTURE-AI working group identified four guiding principles for trustworthy AI in medical imaging: (1) transparency, (2) explainability, (3) fairness, and (4) accountability. The FUTURE-AI working group also identified a set of consensus recommendations for trustworthy AI in medical imaging, including recommendations for the development, validation, and implementation of AI systems. The FUTURE-AI working group's recommendations are intended to guide the development of trustworthy AI systems in medical imaging and to promote the safe and effective use of AI in clinical practice.

\textbf{Keywords}

Artificial intelligence, medical imaging, radiology, ethics, transparency, explainability, fairness, accountability

